<headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 16 at 9:08PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IS IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT FOR
HURON...TUSCOLA...AND SANILAC COUNTIES...
HAZARDS...An area of heavy snow which can rapidly reduce visibility
to a quarter of a mile with rate near 1 inch per hour. Roads remain
slick and hazardous in the Advisory area.
LOCATION AND MOVEMENT...At 905 PM EST, an area of heavy snow was
along a line from near Bay City to near Caro to near Sandusky and
moving southeast at 20 MPH.
THIS AREA OF HEAVY SNOW WILL BE NEAR...
Cass City around 930 PM EST.
Reese, Carsonville and Quanicassee around 945 PM EST.
Applegate around 955 PM EST.
Port Sanilac and Fairgrove around 1005 PM EST.
Unionville around 1020 PM EST.
Deckerville around 1045 PM EST.
SAFETY INFO...
Be prepared for snow or ice covered roads. Slow down
and allow extra time to reach your destination.
&amp;&amp;</description>
